In a speech delivered in Poland, President Donald Trump emphasized the importance of the West's will to survive and its ability to defend its values. He highlighted the role of strong families and strong values in maintaining the strength of a nation. Trump also spoke about the threats of terrorism and extremism, calling for unity in driving out these forces. He emphasized the need to protect individual freedom and sovereignty and to preserve the bonds of culture, faith, and tradition. Trump concluded by expressing the importance of knowing and preserving history in order to build a strong future.